column5: Its been a long wait but its time to get back to Simcoe for some lakers and Whities. Headed out this morning and fished Kemp for about a hour. we managed 5 Lakers between the 2 of us between 1.5-8lbs All fish tight on bottom in 105fow on a williams.  ice seemed good, about 4" of black ice a few cracks here and there. By no means does that speak for the whole lake.   Only had the cellphone sry for the bad pic   Ryan
Glad to hear you did well !!! and it seems that some of the trout grounds are starting to produce..nice trout !!!...cheers
Nice fish!  Were you on foot?  HOw far from shore do you have to go to hit a depth like that?
Great report and pic troutguy Real nice looking lakers for sure, congratulations  Thanks for sharing Leechman

Great set up you got there....lol...from another fan of the x67c  Fat trout, ive been fishing really shallow so far this year...but love pulling them up from deep, specially when the have peeled a good deal of line out too...makes for a long hard fight.  Thanks for sharing...i'm heading out in abbout 2 hours for some trout too....   Thanks for sharing.
Good Job... thats some deep fishin'
Simcoe ice in the laker zone -- nice!!!  Thanks for sharing
